text.tspan: If you have been Emperor for one round only, roll the Imperial
Die. If you roll the Imperial Eagle, you survive. If you roll a skull
(3/6) you die. You die automatically if you have been Emperor
for two rounds, or left the Empire to become a Foreign Power. If
you die as the Emperor, or abdicate, an Imperial Election is
held.
1. The Emperor is elected by the 7 Electors of the Holy Roman
Empire.
2. Players allied to Electors control their votes.
3. Only a Player may receive votes for Emperor.
4. Players may vote for whomever they wish, including
themselves and Players of a different religion from themselves
or the Electors whose votes they control. Any Player may
become Emperor, including Foreign Powers.
5. A Player may not refuse election or re-election, even if he
abdicated.
6. Players attempt to secure the votes of a majority of the
Electors (4) to be elected Emperor. Unaligned Electors vote as a
block for the Player of their religion with the most votes after all
Players have voted. Initiative/Setup Order between tied Players.
If a majority cannot be secured, the Emperor may be elected by
a plurality.
7. Give the newly elected Emperor the Emperor Card, and place
the Imperial Die on the Round #/Year.
- Gain 1 DI if Foreign Powers (other than yourself) own zero
provinces in the Empire or you and your allies conquered at
least one province from a Foreign Power.
- Lose 3 DI if Foreign Powers (other than yourself) own
provinces in the Empire and you did not fight in a war against a
Foreign Power.
